sub_title: Training to become a field guide, climate and development research background
summary: I am a determined and goal-orientated International Development and Physical Geography masters graduate. I am currently working as a researcher contributing towards the 2025 UN year of the glacier and spend a lot of my winter in the backcountry and summer hiking/ climbing mountains training to become a field and mountain guide. As an accomplished communicator, I enjoy working with others and I have an open and friendly personality. My listening skills are essential and can help to build trust in every work place. Through my experience I feel strongly that collaboration is paramount for a successful workplace. The ability to work well under pressure individually, or in a team environment, has been the key factor in my work experience to date.
